           function customItemTeaserDisplay() {

              return '';
          } else {
              var answerCount = TurnToItemData.counts.a;
              var questionCount = TurnToItemData.counts.q;
              var teaserContainer = TurnTojQuery(".TurnToItemTeaser");
              var teaserHtml = '';
              if (questionCount > 0) {
                  teaserHtml += '<a data-t-events="A" data-t-e-var78 = "$ - See QA"  id="readQuestions" href="javascript:void(0)">';
                  teaserHtml +='See <strong>' + questionCount + '</strong> Question' + (questionCount == 1 ? '' : 's');
                  if(answerCount > 0){
                      teaserHtml +=' | <strong>' + answerCount + '</strong> Answer' + (answerCount == 1 ? '' : 's');
                  }
                  teaserHtml +='</a>';
              } else {
                  teaserHtml += '<a data-t-events="A" data-t-e-var78 = "$ - Ask Or Answer"  id="readQuestions" href="javascript:void(0)">Ask Or Answer A Question </a>';
              }
              jQuery("#turntolinks").html(teaserHtml);
              jQuery("#Customer-QA_Tab")[0].setAttribute("style", "display:block");
              jQuery("#readQuestions").click(function (e) {
                  e.preventDefault();
                  jQuery("#tabSections li").removeClass("active");
                  jQuery("#tabSections li").eq(4).addClass("active");
                  Biz.Product.CrossTable.scrollToQA();
              });
          }
      }

      var turnToConfig = {
          siteKey: "SZTRUjeBj9oQlLYsite",
          setupType: "dynamicEmbed",
          iTeaserFunc: customItemTeaserDisplay,
          skipCssLoad: true
      };
      (function() {
        var tt = document.createElement('script'); tt.type = 'text/javascript'; tt.async = true;
        tt.src = document.location.protocol + "//static.www.turnto.com/traServer4_2/trajs/" + turnToConfig.siteKey + "/tra.js";
        var s = document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0]; s.parentNode.insertBefore(tt, s);
      })();
      </script>

      var TurnToItemSku = "N82E16813128972";
    </script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="//static.www.turnto.com/sitedata/SZTRUjeBj9oQlLYsite/v4_2/N82E16813128972/d/itemjs"></script>

<div class="rn-boxContent">


<div id="Overview_Content" class="grpContent Overview_Content inactive">



            <div class="itmDesc" id="introduction">
                <div style="background-color:black; color:white;">







<img style="float:left; padding:30px 0 0 130px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/logo.jpg" alt="general information">



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>







<p style="text-align:center;padding:10px 0 30px 0;">

         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/title.jpg" alt="general information">

</p>



<div style="width:100%; height:432px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/mb_board_1366.jpg) no-repeat right center; ">





<img style="float:left; padding:50px 0 0 60px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/features1.png" alt="general information">



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>

</div>





 <p style="padding:30px 35px 10px 35px; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">Build a devastatingly powerful gaming rig with the GIGABYTE GA-Z270XP-SLI motherboard. Constructed of high-quality components, packed with exclusive gaming features and loaded with Smart Fan 5 for maximum cooling performance, it brings gamers and VR professionals the best possible gaming experience. </p>







<img style="float:right; padding:10px 20px 0 20px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/features.png" alt="general information">



<div style="padding-right:390px;">



<p style="padding:10px 0 0 45px;font-size:1.2em;"><strong>At a Glance</strong></p>





<ul style="padding:0 0 0 65px; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; list-style-type:square; list-style-position:outside;">





<li>Supports 7th/ 6th Generation Intel Core Processors</li>



<li>Dual Channel Non-ECC Unbuffered DDR4, 4 DIMMs</li>



<li>Fast USB 3.1 Gen 2 with USB Type-C nd Type-A</li>



<li>2-Way SLI 3-Way CrossFire Multi-Graphics Support</li>



<li>Dual NVMe PCIe SSDs in RAID 0 Support</li>

<li>Intel Optane Memory Ready</li>

<li>VR Ready</li>


<li>Ultra-Fast M.2 with PCIe Gen3 x4 &amp; SATA interface</li>


<li>ALC1220 120dB SNR HD Audio with Smart Headphone Amp</li>

<li>High Quality Audio Capacitors and Audio Noise Guard with LED Trace Path Lighting</li>



<li>Intel GbE LAN with cFosSpeed Internet Accelerator Software</li>

<li>Smart Fan 5 features Multiple Temperature Sensors and Hybrid Fan Headers</li>

<li>Lightning-Fast Intel Thunderbolt 3 AIC Support</li>

<li>GIGABYTE UEFI DualBIO</li>

<li>APP Center Including EasyTune and Cloud Station Utilities</li>

</ul>





<img style="float:left; padding:0 0 40px 65px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/3826.png" alt="general information">



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto;"></div>





</div>







<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>





<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>









<div style="text-align:center; padding-top:30px;">







<div style="display:inline-block; width:45%; text-align:center; margin:0 0 10px; padding:0; vertical-align:top;">



<img style="margin-bottom:10px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/1B.jpg" alt="hardware">



<p style="text-align:left; margin-left:30px; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">With Smart Fan 5 users can ensure that their gaming PC can maintain its performance while staying cool. Smart Fan 5 allows users to interchange their fan headers to reflect different thermal sensors at different locations on the motherboard. Not only that, with Smart Fan 5 more hybrid fan headers that support both PWM and Voltage mode fans have been introduced to make the motherboard more liquid cooling friendly.</p>



</div>







<div style="display:inline-block; width:45%; text-align:center; margin:0 0 10px; padding:0; vertical-align:top;">



<img style="margin-bottom:10px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/1cv.jpg" alt="hardware">



</div>





</div>

















<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>









<div style="padding:20px 0;">





<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E;">All Hybrid Fan Pin Headers</p>







<ul style="padding:0 25px 0 45px; list-style-position:outside; width:55%; margin:auto; list-style-type:square; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; ">



<li>All Hybrid Fan Headers can automatically detect the type of cooling device whether it be fan or pump with different PWM or Voltage mode.</li>



<li>Supports up to 2 amps with built-in overcurrent protection - a must for high-end high current fans.</li>



</ul>





</div>







<p style="text-align:center;padding:0 0 20px 0; ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/2.jpg" alt="general information">



</p>





<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>







<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:20px 0 0 0;">New Smart Fan 5 Software</p>







<p style="padding:0 35px 10px 35px; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">Choose from different modes, Quiet to Full Speed, to match your system usage scenario. For each fan or pump, you can use the intuitive fan curve to define trigger thresholds and corresponding fan speeds. </p>











<img style="float:right; padding:10px 50px 0 20px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/3.jpg" alt="general information">



<div style="padding-right:370px;line-height:1.6em;">



<p style="padding:60px 0 0 45px;font-size:1.2em; font-weight:bold;">Interoperable Sensors and Fans



</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em; ">Each fan can be customized to operate at different speeds according to any defined temperature source input (except the CPU fan).</p>



</div>



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 1em;"></div>









<img style="float:left; padding:10px 20px 0 50px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/4.jpg" alt="general information">



<div style="padding-left:370px; line-height:1.6em;">



<p style="padding:60px 45px 0 0;font-size:1.2em;font-weight:bold; ">Fan Curve</p>



<p style="padding:0 45px 0 0; font-size:1.1em;">Customize fan curves based on specific temperatures with the intuitive graphical UI.</p>



</div>



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>



<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>







<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:20px 0 0 0;">Enhanced BIOS Interface</p>





<p style="padding:0 35px 10px 35px; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">The enhanced BIOS interface also has the advanced features seen in the Smart Fan 5 UI, such as: the ability to set triggers based on different temperature sensors on the board, fan curve definition and the temperature interval setting, which can prevent fan rotation noise caused by sudden temperature change - all without having to load Windows.</p>

<p style="text-align:center;padding:10px 0 20px 0; ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/5.jpg" alt="general information">



</p>







<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>





<div style="width:100%; height:800px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/6.jpg) no-repeat center center; ">







<img style="float:left; padding:10px 20px 0 50px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/6b.png" alt="general information">



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 1em;"></div>





<div style="padding:10px 445px 0 25px;">



<div style="padding:30px 20px; background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);">



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E;">Immersive VR Gaming Experience</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em;line-height:1.6em;">-   VR requires more performance than Full HD graphics for a steady 90FPS or greater. </p>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em;line-height:1.6em;">-   Only Gaming PCs can provide the best VR experience.</p>



</div>

</div>







<p style="text-align:center; ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/6a.png" alt="general information">



</p>





</div>



<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>



 <div style="padding-right:90px;">





<p style="padding:30px 0 0 45px;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E;">ALC 1220 120dB SNR HD Audio with Smart Headphone Amp</p>



<img style="float:left; padding:10px 20px 0 50px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/ALC1220.jpg" alt="general information">

<div style="padding-left:370px;">

<p style="padding:60px 45px 0 0 ; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">Exceptional audio listening experience with 120dB SNR and support for DSD128 hardware decode. Smart Headphone AMP automatically adjusts volumes based on detected headphone impedance.</p>

</div>

<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>

</div>







<p style="padding:10px 0 0 0 ;font-size:1.2em; font-weight:bold; text-align:center;">Smart Headphone Amp</p>



<p style="width:65%;margin:auto; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;text-align:center;">Automatically detects impedance of your head-worn audio device, whether earbuds or high-end headphones to provide optimal audio dynamics - preventing issues such as low volume and distortion.</p>

<p style="text-align:center;padding:30px 0;">

         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/mb_headphone.jpg" alt="General information">

</p>






<div style="text-align:center;">
<img style="width:300px; margin:2px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/auiocaptor.jpg" alt="viewing">
<img style="width:360px; margin:2px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/amp.jpg" alt="viewing">

</div>






 <div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>











<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;">Intel GbE LAN with cFosSpeed Internet Accelerator Software</p>





<p style="padding:0 0 10px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:65%; margin:auto;">Intel Gigabit LAN features cFosSpeed, a network traffic management application which helps to improve network latency and maintain low ping times to deliver better responsiveness in crowded LAN environments.</p>



<img style="float:left; padding:30px 0 0 320px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/8a1.jpg" alt="general information">

<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto;"></div>



<p style="text-align:center; ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/8a.png" alt="general information">



</p>



<p style="text-align:center; width:55%; margin:auto; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;color:#FFD80E; padding:5px 0 20px 0;">cFosSpeed Internet Accelerator Software</p>





<div style="width:100%; height:157px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/8b.png) no-repeat center center; ">



</div>







<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>









<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0; width:85%; margin:auto;">

Fast Onboard Storage with NVMe PCIe Gen3 x4 110mm M.2 (Up to 32 Gbps)

</p>





<p style="padding:10px 0 10px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:65%; margin:auto;">GIGABYTE M.2 solution offers considerably faster storage performance and support for both PCIe and SATA interfaces for M.2 SSD devices.</p>





 <div style="text-align:center;padding:20px 0;">



<img style="width:420px; margin:2px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/9c.jpg" alt="viewing">

<img style="width:380px; margin:2px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/9d.jpg" alt="viewing">



</div>





<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>





 <div style="width:100%; height:367px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/9.jpg) no-repeat right center; ">



<p style="padding:8% 45% 0 10%; font-size:1.8em; color:#FFD80E;">2-Way SLI / 3-Way CrossFire Multi Graphics</p><p>

  </p><p style="padding:0 45% 0 10%; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">Multi-graphics configuration offers better graphics performance for gaming enthusiasts who demand the highest frame rates without compromising on resolution.</p><p>





</p></div>





<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>





 <div style="padding-right:60px;">









<img style="float:left; padding:10px 20px 0 50px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/10.png" alt="general information">

<div style="padding-left:370px;">



<p style="padding:30px 0 0 0;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E;">

PURE SPEED

</p>

<p style="padding:0 45px 0 0 ;font-size:1.2em; font-weight:bold;">GIGABYTE Extreme <span style="font-size:1.6em; color:#FFD80E;background-color:#ffffff;padding:5px 3px;">USB 3.1</span> Motherboards</p>

<p style="padding:0 45px 0 0 ; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">The ASMEDIA 2142 USB 3.1 controller utilizes 2 PCIe Gen3 lanes, offering a total of up to 16 Gbps, which means you have extra bandwidth to take full control of the 10 Gbps USB 3.1 ports. With twice the bandwidth compared to its previous generation, and backwards compatibility with USB 2.0 and 3.0, the much improved USB 3.1 protocol is available over the new reversible USB Type-C and the traditional USB Type-A connector for better compatibility over a wider range of devices.</p>

</div>

<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>

</div>





 <p style="text-align:center; ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/11.png" alt="general information">



</p>



<p style="text-align:center; width:55%; margin:auto; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;color:#FFD80E; padding:5px 0 20px 0;">Max. bandwidth allocated for the controller may vary by model</p>





 <p style="text-align:center; ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/12.png" alt="general information">



</p>







 <div style="width:75%; margin:auto;">





<img style="float:right; padding:10px 50px 0 20px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/13.png" alt="general information">

<div style="padding-right:370px;">

<p style="padding:30px 0 0 45px;font-size:1.2em;font-weight:bold;">

Connecting the Future - USB Type-C

</p>

<p style="padding:0  0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;"> - The World's Next Universal Connector</p>

<p style="padding:0  0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;"> - Reversible USB Type-C with USB 3.1 Gen 2</p>



</div>

<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 1em;"></div>

</div>

 <div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>







 <div style="width:100%; height:584px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/14.jpg) no-repeat right center; ">



<div style="padding:10px 445px 0 25px;">



<div style="padding:30px 20px; background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);">



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E;">Support for DDR4 XMP Up to 3866MHz and Beyond*</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em;line-height:1.6em;">GIGABYTE is offering a tested and proven platform that ensures proper compatibility with profiles up to 3866MHz and beyond. All users need to do to attain this performance boost is to ensure that their memory module is XMP capable and that the XMP function is activated and enabled on GIGABYTE motherboard.</p>

</div>

</div>

<p style="text-align:center;padding:10px 0 0 0;  ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/14.png" alt="general information">

</p>





</div>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E;">What is XMP?</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em;line-height:1.6em;">DDR4 memory modules are available at a stock frequency of 2133MHz, but as frequency tweaking requires a considerable amount of effort and knowledge, memory vendors encode XMP profiles which can automatically modify the timings of the supported memory modules to work with your CPU and to achieve increased performance.</p>



 <p style="padding:0 0 20px 45px;line-height:1.6em;">

* XMP Profile support may vary depending on memory module. Product features may vary by model.

</p>

  <div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>









  <p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:60px 0 0 0; width:85%; margin:auto;">



GIGABYTE Exclusive Double Locking Bracket





</p>

   <p style="text-align:center;padding:40px 0 50px 0;  ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/18a.jpg" alt="general information">

</p>



         <div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>









<div style="width:100%; height:625px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/16.jpg) no-repeat center center; ">



<div style="padding-top:230px;">



<div style="width:60%; margin:auto;  padding:30px 20px; background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);">



<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; ">



Anti-Sulfur Resistor Design



</p>





<p style="font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">Sulfur compounds in the air can penetrate tiny onboard resistors creating chemical change and causing these resistors to fail open or short. If either of these occurs the motherboard will fail to function. By equipping resistors with an Anti-Sulfur Design GIGABYTE gives Ultra Durable Motherboards a whole new meaning.</p>



</div>



</div>

</div>







<div style="text-align:center; padding:0 0 20px 0;">



<img style="width:380px; margin:2px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/16a.png" alt="viewing">



<img style="width:380px; margin:2px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/16b.png" alt="viewing">





</div>







    <div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>





  <div style="padding-left:90px;">





<img style="float:right; padding:10px 50px 0 20px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/auiocaptor.jpg" alt="general information">

<div style="padding-right:370px;">

<p style="padding:30px 0 0 45px;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E;">

Diagnostic LEDs

</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px;font-size:1.2em;font-weight:bold;">



</p>

<p style="padding:0  0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em;">Onboard LEDs controlled by the system BIOS indicate if a malfunction is occurring, allowing users to quickly diagnose which major component (CPU/DDR/VGA/HDD) is malfunctioning so they may take action promptly.</p>

<p style="padding:0  0 0 45px; line-height:1.6em;">*The photo is for reference only.</p>

</div>



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>

</div>







    <div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>





         <p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;">Refreshed BIOS Easy, Smart, and Friendly</p>





<p style="padding:0 0 10px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:75%; margin:auto;">The BIOS is essential for users during initial setup to allow for the most optimal settings. With a new GUI and easier-to-use functionalities, GIGABYTE has been able to reinvent the BIOS to give users a better experience while setting up their new system.</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 10px 0; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:65%; margin:auto; font-style:italic;">(The below photos are for reference only.)</p>







<div style="width:100%; height:482px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-980/14.jpg) no-repeat center center; "></div>







<img style="float:right; padding:30px 50px 0 20px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-980/15.jpg" alt="general information">



<div style="padding-right:370px;">



<p style="padding:30px 0 0 45px;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E;">GIGABYTE APP Center</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em;line-height:1.6em;">The GIGABYTE APP Center gives you easy access to a wealth of GIGABYTE apps that help you get the most from your GIGABYTE motherboard. Using a simple, unified user interface, GIGABYTE APP Center allows you to easily launch all GIGABYTE apps installed on your system, check related updates online, and download the latest apps, drivers, and BIOS.</p>



</div>



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>







<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;">EasyTune</p>





<p style="padding:0 0 30px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:75%; margin:auto;">GIGABYTE's EasyTune is a simple and easy-to-use interface that allows users to fine-tune their system settings or adjust system and memory clocks and voltages in a Windows environment. With Smart Quick Boost, one click is all it takes to automatically overclock your system, giving an added performance boost when you need it the most.</p>





<div style="width:100%; height:218px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/all_easytune.gif) no-repeat center center; "></div>







         <p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;"> Overclocking to Boost Your Frame Rates

</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 30px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:75%; margin:auto;">Get the highest levels of performance from your PC with easy-to-use GIGABYTE overclocking features.



</p>









<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;">System Information Viewer</p>





<p style="padding:0 0 30px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:75%; margin:auto;">GIGABYTE System Information Viewer is a central location that gives you access to your current system status. Monitor components such as the clocks and processor, set your preferred fan speed profile, create alerts when temperatures get too high or record your system’s behavior; these are the possibilities of the System Information Viewer.</p>





<div style="width:100%; height:268px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/145/13-145-007/16.gif) no-repeat center center; "></div>









         <p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:40px 0 0 0;">@BIOS</p>





<p style="padding:0 0 15px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:75%; margin:auto;">The GIGABYTE @BIOS app allows you to update your system’s BIOS from within Windows using a simple and slick graphical user interface. @BIOS can automatically download the latest version from the GIGABYTE servers or you can update your BIOS from a file on your computer. @BIOS also allows you to save your current BIOS to a file, recover your previous BIOS from an image and backup your BIOS to an image.</p>







<p style="text-align:center; ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/145/13-145-007/17.gif" alt="general information">



</p>







<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;">3D OSD</p>





<p style="padding:0 0 10px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:70%; margin:auto;">3D OSD automatically detects and displays your system information during games, allowing you to easily get a hold of your system information without switching between screens.</p>







<div style="width:100%; height:372px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/145/13-145-007/18.gif) no-repeat center center; "></div>





<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>







<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;">GIGABYTE Exclusive DualBIOS (UEFI) Design</p>





<p style="padding:0 0 10px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:85%; margin:auto;">GIGABYTE Ultra Durable motherboards feature GIGABYTE DualBIOS, an exclusive technology from GIGABYTE that protects arguably one of your PC's most crucial components, the BIOS. GIGABYTE DualBIOS means that your motherboard has both a 'Main BIOS' and a 'Backup BIOS', protecting users from BIOS failure due to virus, hardware malfunction, improper OC settings or power failure during the update process.</p>





<p style="text-align:center;padding:10px 0 20px 0; ">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-980/19.jpg" alt="general information">



</p>



<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>





<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;">Easy-to-install "G-Connector" Design</p>





 <p style="padding:0 0 10px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:85%; margin:auto;">The tiny cables of the front panel connectors can be hard to manipulate as space is restricted and indicators being tiny. With the G-Connector, you can connect all the FP cables at once, simplifying the process of building your next PC and saving you some frustrations.</p>





<p style="text-align:center;padding:20px 0 30px 0;">



         <img src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-972/21.jpg" alt="general information">



</p>







<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>





<img style="float:left; padding:30px 20px 0 50px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-980/20.jpg" alt="general information">



<div style="padding-left:370px;">



<p style="padding:30px 45px 0 0;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E; ">4K Ultra HD Support</p>



<p style="padding:0 45px 0 0; font-size:1.1em;line-height:1.6em;">4K resolution is the next technological milestone in high-definition content delivery, utilizing approximately 4,000 pixels on the horizontal axis, more than four times today's standard HD pixel density. GIGABYTE motherboards provide native 4K support with integrated Intel HD Graphics via HDMI.</p>



</div>



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>





<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>



<img style="float:right; padding:90px 50px 0 20px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-980/21.jpg" alt="general information">



<div style="padding-right:370px;">



<p style="padding:20px 0 0 45px;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E;">HDMI - The Next Generation Multimedia Interface</p>



<p style="padding:0 0 0 45px; font-size:1.1em;line-height:1.6em;">HDMI is a High-Definition Multimedia Interface which provides up to 5Gbps video transmitting bandwidth and 8-channel high quality audio all through a single cable. Able to transmit superior, uncompressed digital video and audio, HDMI ensures the crispest rendering of digital content up to 1080p without the quality losses associated with analog interfaces and their digital-to-analog conversion. In addition, HDMI is compatible with HDCP (High-bandwidth Digital Content Protection), allowing the playback of Blu-ray/HD DVD and other protected media content.</p>



</div>



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>





<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>



<img style="float:left; padding:40px 20px 0 50px;" src="//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-980/22.jpg" alt="general information">



<div style="padding-left:370px;">



<p style="padding:30px 45px 0 0;font-size:1.8em;color:#FFD80E; ">



XSplit Gamecaster + Broadcaster: Cast Your Game Anytime, Anywhere



</p>



<p style="padding:0 45px 0 0; font-size:1.1em;line-height:1.6em;">Now set up your stage and share the greatest gaming moments with XSplit Gamecaster + Broadcaster! Fully optimized social media integration is ready for real-time chats - keeping you notified yet focused in the game. It takes just one click to stream your gameplay to Twitch. Host your game like a pro!</p>



</div>



<div style="width:100%; clear:both; margin:0 auto 2em;"></div>





<div style="height:0.5px; border-top:0.5px solid #d4d4d4; margin:10px 0;">  </div>













<div style="width:100%; height:588px; margin-bottom:0; background:url(//images10.newegg.com/BizIntell/item/13/128/13-128-980/23.jpg) no-repeat center center; ">





<p style="font-size:1.8em; text-align:center; color:#FFD80E; padding:30px 0 0 0;">TriDef SmartCam | Custom Stream Modding</p>





<p style="padding:0 0 10px 0; font-size:1.1em; line-height:1.6em; text-align:center; width:85%; margin:auto;">To facilitate being the full streaming solution each GIGABYTE motherboard includes TriDef SmartCam software, you are now able to remove backgrounds without the hassle of using a green screen. Through the SmartCam application you can now apply live filters, and fully control your background, not only while streaming, but also through other video applications such as Skype.</p>









</div>

















</div>

Spec</h3><legend style="display:none;">|</legend><dl><dt>Form Factor</dt><dd>ATX</dd></dl><dl><dt>Dimensions (W x L)</dt><dd>12.0" x 8.9"</dd></dl><dl><dt>Power Pin</dt><dd>1 x 24-pin ATX main power connector<br>1 x 8-pin ATX 12V power connector</dd></dl></fieldset><fieldset><h3 class="specTitle">Features</h3><legend style="display:none;">|</legend><dl><dt>Features</dt><dd>Multi-Graphics Technology:<br>Support for NVIDIA Quad-GPU SLI and 2-Way NVIDIA SLI technologies<br>Support for AMD Quad-GPU CrossFireX and 3-Way/2-Way AMD CrossFire technologies<br><br>I/O Controller:<br>iTE I/O Controller Chip<br><br>H/W Monitoring:<br>Voltage detection<br>Temperature detection<br>Fan speed detection<br>Overheating warning<br>Fan fail warning<br>Fan speed control<br>* Whether the fan (pump) speed control function is supported will depend on the fan (pump) you install.<br><br>BIOS:<br>2 x 64 Mbit flash<br>Use of licensed AMI UEFI BIOS<br>Support for DualBIOS<br>PnP 1.0a, DMI 2.7, WfM 2.0, SM BIOS 2.7, ACPI 5.0<br><br>Unique Features:<br>Support for APP Center<br>* Available applications in APP Center may vary by motherboard model. Supported functions of each application may also vary depending on motherboard specifications.<br>3D OSD<br>@BIOS<br>Ambient LED<br>AutoGreen<br>BIOS Setup<br>Color Temperature<br>Cloud Station<br>EasyTune<br>Easy RAID<br>Fast Boot<br>Game Boost<br>ON/OFF Charge<br>Platform Power Management<br>Smart Backup<br>Smart Keyboard<br>Smart TimeLock<br>System Information Viewer<br>USB Blocker<br>V-Tuner<br>Support for 3TB+ Unlock<br>Support for Q-Flash<br>Support for Xpress Install<br><br>Bundle Software:<br>Norton Internet Security (OEM version)<br>Intel Optane Memory Ready<br>cFosSpeed<br><br>Operating System:<br>Windows 10 64-bit (for 7th Generation Intel Processors)<br>Windows 10 64-bit / Windows 8.1 64-bit / Windows 7 32-bit / 64-bit (for 6th Generation Intel Processors)<br>* Please download the "Windows USB Installation Tool" from GIGABYTE's website and install it before installing Windows 7.</dd></dl></fieldset>
    </div>
</div>

                        }

        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating" style="display:none;">

            <span class="comments-title-content" itemprop="name">So far, so good</span>

        <span class="comments-text comments-time comments-time-right" itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-05-12" "="">5/12/2018 7:31:14 AM</span>
    </div>




                    <div class="comments-cell-body">
                        <div class="comments-cell-body-inner">




<div class="comments-content" itemprop="reviewBody">


            <p>
                <strong>Pros:</strong>
                - Plenty of fan headers<br>- USB C<br>- Pretty easy to manage cables with this board.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Cons:</strong>
                - PS/2 ports <br>- Janky looking BIOS/UEFI screen
            </p>


        <p>
            <strong>Other Thoughts:</strong>
            I with Gigabyte and all other manufacturers would stop putting PS/2 ports on their montherboards. I think USB keyboards are ubiquitous enough and work reliably enough with BIOS now that we don't need to worry about falling back on some ancient keyboard and mouse connectors. Give me more USB ports instead!<br><br>To elaborate further on the BIOS/UEFI screens, unless you are using an old 4:3 monitor, the BIOS is stretched out on a widescreen display. This seems to also happen with the Windows boot logo if you use UEFI. It looks really unpolished.
        </p>

</div>

<div class="comments-cell-side">
    <div class="comments-name" itemprop="author"><a href="https://www.newegg.com/profile/reviews/ekJqcHM3TW1oYTdnMzYvM3lad3JUb2dUUEFUZGhUTnk=" title="View BRIAN K.'s Profile" data-t-events="A" data-t-e-var78="$ - Profile:ekJqcHM3TW1oYTdnMzYvM3lad3JUb2dUUEFUZGhUTnk=">BRIAN K.</a></div>

            <div class="comments-cell-body">
                <div class="comments-cell-body-inner">


    <div class="comments-title">

        <i class="rating rating-2"></i>
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating" style="display:none;">
            <meta itemprop="worstRating" content="1">
            <span itemprop="ratingValue">2</span>/
            <span itemprop="bestRating">5</span>
        </div>

            <span class="comments-title-content" itemprop="name">There are much better options for the money</span>

        <span class="comments-text comments-time comments-time-right" itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-03-29" "="">3/29/2018 7:50:27 PM</span>
    </div>




                    <div class="comments-cell-body">
                        <div class="comments-cell-body-inner">




<div class="comments-content" itemprop="reviewBody">


            <p>
                <strong>Pros:</strong>
                -Worked for a very basic setup without overclocking on an i5-7600k and ddr4 3000 memory.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Cons:</strong>
                -Flimsy, as stated in previous review.<br>-When I changed ANY hardware on the board, it would cause great frustration and eventually died.  An upgraded GPU wreaked havoc on the bootup process even when first completely removing the old drivers and resetting the BIOS.  The board simply didn't output any video to any port, either onboard or the GPUs.<br>-The 3rd PCIe slot simply stopped working one day on it's own which was neat. <br>-Gigabyte's software is as terrible as any others.<br>-For fun, I attempted to overclock with this board since I had a better quality board on the way.  The board died immediately and wouldn't boot with a 4.3Ghz clock.  The CPU was just fine and has been overclocked on the new board for 2 months at 4.9Ghz.
            </p>


        <p>
            <strong>Other Thoughts:</strong>
            Even with the rebate knocking this down to $100, it still wasn't worth it.  There are lots of these listed as broken on auction sites for a reason.
        </p>

</div>

            <div class="comments-cell-body">
                <div class="comments-cell-body-inner">


    <div class="comments-title">

        <i class="rating rating-5"></i>
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating" style="display:none;">
            <meta itemprop="worstRating" content="1">
            <span itemprop="ratingValue">5</span>/
            <span itemprop="bestRating">5</span>
        </div>

            <span class="comments-title-content" itemprop="name">GA-270XP-SLI motherboard.</span>

        <span class="comments-text comments-time comments-time-right" itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-02-27" "="">2/27/2018 11:21:47 AM</span>
    </div>




                    <div class="comments-cell-body">
                        <div class="comments-cell-body-inner">




<div class="comments-content" itemprop="reviewBody">


            <p>
                <strong>Pros:</strong>
                All the holes lined up, and fit perfect in the ATX case. <br>Booted up, no problems at all, and has been running fine since then. <br>It scores well with a 7700K CPU, on Mark 7, so I was happy with that.  The added Apps, allow easy control of this board. <br>No real  complaints on this board at all, with the exception of the CD drivers (see Cons for more details).
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Cons:</strong>
                After I had installed Windows 7, I started to install the drivers from the CD that came with it. <br>On the Universal SBC 3.0 driver, when it installed, it locked Windows up solid.  I had to uninstall Windows 7, and do a <br>complete install.  After the Install, I loaded in all the drivers, but that one.  Then went to the Gigabyte Web site, and downloaded <br>the newest version, and that installed fine.  I am not sure if I just got a faulty disk, or if this driver has an issue with Win 7.  <br>Other than that minor issue, the Board is rock solid.
            </p>


        <p>
            <strong>Other Thoughts:</strong>
            Yes, I would recommend this board to anyone I  know.
        </p>

</div>

                        <div class="comments-cell-body-inner">




<div class="comments-content" itemprop="reviewBody">


            <p>
                <strong>Pros:</strong>
                Easy to set up. Easy to manage and use bios. They don't lie when they say this motherboard is durable!
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Cons:</strong>
                There wasn't a Molex connector for my case fans, but I was glad they included extra fan connectors on the board!
            </p>


</div>

            <span itemprop="ratingValue">1</span>/

            <span class="comments-title-content" itemprop="name">Buyer beware!</span>

        <span class="comments-text comments-time comments-time-right" itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-01-19" "="">1/19/2018 11:10:27 PM</span>
    </div>




                    <div class="comments-cell-body">
                        <div class="comments-cell-body-inner">




<div class="comments-content" itemprop="reviewBody">


            <p>
                <strong>Pros:</strong>
                None...yet.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Cons:</strong>
                Cheap price--now I know why.
            </p>


        <p>
            <strong>Other Thoughts:</strong>
            Bought this to replace an Asus Z270-P that I bought from Newegg with damaged pins--system would power up but not post--closer inspection revealed damaged pins and I'm stuck with this brick.<br><br>Got the CPU installed, GPU and RAM in place--system will power on for 20 seconds then shut down, power up for another 15-20 seconds, then shut down and won't power back up unless I unplug the PSU.  Tomorrow morning I'm swapping out my brand new PSU for another brand new PSU to eliminate a bad PSU possiblity.  After further review I found these issues are common to all Z270 boards and the Gigabyte model has even more problems--buyer beware:<br><br>Currently, on most Gigabyte Z270 boards the latest BIOS that enables "Intel Optane Memory" is causing issues with XMP profiles. The issue forces the motherboard to power off when restarting and then power back on.<br><br>To be clear, when the user prompts Windows to restart the system it will then go through the motions but cut power entirely to your system before powering back on ONLY when XMP is enabled in the latest BIOS. Cutting power abruptly and constantly is ill advised.<br><br>This issue can only be remedied in two ways: downgrade your BIOS or disable XMP. Downgrading your BIOS with the integrated Qflash is impossible as the latest BIOS on these boards prohibits going to older BIOS versions. The method for flashing back is very dangerous and ill advised.<br><br>Some boards come with the latest BIOS from the manufacturer and others do not, it is a gamble.<br><br>EDIT: This issue persists even if you manually dial in the ram speeds advertised on the XMP profile. It will not allow you to run the memory at the advertised speeds even if it is compatible with the board using the latest BIOS.<br><br>Gigabyte support says this is a serious issue and has made it a high priority.<br><br>Gigabyte Statement<br><br>Gigabyte is privately giving out fixed BIOS versions for certain boards. Keep in mind, these BIOS updates have not been made available on the support site, they have not been made available for every board, and are being "selectively handed out" to complaining customers.<br><br>ASSUMPTION: Huge issue with Gigabyte BIOS programmers. This was a massive oversight and is taking far too long to rectify.
        </p>

</div>






<div class="comments-helpful has-button">

            <span class="comments-title-content" itemprop="name">Having problems with the sound</span>

        <span class="comments-text comments-time comments-time-right" itemprop="datePublished" content="2017-11-26" "="">11/26/2017 9:58:11 PM</span>
    </div>




                    <div class="comments-cell-body">
                        <div class="comments-cell-body-inner">




<div class="comments-content" itemprop="reviewBody">


            <p>
                <strong>Pros:</strong>
                -Lots of good things like the newest USB, combined with gaming features
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Cons:</strong>
                I've had 2 problems with this board, 1 that I was able to resolve and 1 that I'm waiting to hear back from Gigabyte about. The first problem is that once I got my computer built, I'd get 1 short post beep but nothing was coming up on the screen. I had an old video card that I plugged in so that allowed me to get to the bios, where I found that the onboard video was set to auto yet it obviously wasn't kicking in. I enabled that setting, took the old video card out, and the onboard video started working. This would be a problem if you don't plan on using a dedicated video card and don't have one lying around, though I know that's the minority of users for a board like this. The other issue is that my onboard sound doesn't appear to be working correctly despite having the newest drivers. I tried switching on and off all sorts of audio options. The audio through my speakers works for a few minutes after I restart the computer, and then it randomly stops working. In the audio devices menu, I can see that it's supposedly unplugging and plugging itself back in despite me not touching it. The speakers worked on my last computer so I'm assuming the problem is with the motherboard.
            </p>


</div>

                    </div>
                    <div class="TT4askedByBlock TT3metaText">
                        <span class="TT3askedBy">

                                <a href="javascript:void(0)" rel="nofollow" tt3-uid="9493984">omar g</a>

                                          <div>
                                              <span class="TTbestAnswer">BEST ANSWER:</span> <span id="TT3aText4612962" class="TT3aText">There are two normal PCIE slots, you can use either for a graphics card. If you use two graphics cards on both slots simultaneously, they SLI together (scalable link interface) to produce a single output</span>

        <div id="TT3quest-3197179" class="TT3questWrp TT3questBorder" tt3-uid="10437612" answers="2" date="1515079345000" upvotes="0" downvotes="0" style="">
            <div class="TT3questCntr">
                <div class="TT3itemBox" ttqid="3197179">
                    <div>
                        <span id="TT3qText3197179" class="TT3qText">What is the configuration of the bios to be able to do a mining rig with 6 gpu amd?</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="TT4askedByBlock TT3metaText">
                        <span class="TT3askedBy">

                                <a href="javascript:void(0)" rel="nofollow" tt3-uid="10437612">AurelioLinares</a>

                            <span class="TT3youHolder" tt3-uid="10437612"></span>

                        </span>


                        <span class="TT3timeStamp">
                            on Jan 4, 2018
                        </span>
                    </div>



                        <div id="TT4bestAnswerBlock-3197179" class="TT4bestAnswerBlock">
                          <div class="TT4ansAndReplies">
                            <div class="TT3ansArea" bestanswer="true">
                              <div class="TT2left TT4ansWidth">
                                <div class="TT3ansCntr">
                                      <div class="TT3itemBox2" style="position:relative">
                                          <div>
                                              <span class="TTbestAnswer">BEST ANSWER:</span> <span id="TT3aText4924386" class="TT3aText">It does not support 6 gpus, all though there are 6 pcie and 1 m.2, the sixth gpu will not work. Now even with the bios upgrade. If you want a 6 gpu mining board, check out the z270p-d3 or the z270-d3 (you will need a m.2 pcie 1x adapter), they are the same bios but work great with 6 gpus, the z270p-d3 does 7</span>
                                              <ul class="TT3linkLine">
    <li><a id="TT3replyLink4924386" href="javascript:void(0)" rel="nofollow" onclick="TurnTo.ilr(3197179, 4924386, null, this )">Reply</a>

        <div id="TT3quest-2271251" class="TT3questWrp TT3questBorder" answers="3" date="1486241012000" upvotes="0" downvotes="0" style="">
            <div class="TT3questCntr">
                <div class="TT3itemBox" ttqid="2271251">
                    <div>
                        <span id="TT3qText2271251" class="TT3qText">How exactly does this board support "Dual NVMe RAID 0 Support, M.2", when it has only 1 M.2 slot connector?  I know you can use a pci slot adapter card, but IMO that really defeats the purpose of M.2 slots to begin with......</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="TT4askedByBlock TT3metaText">
                        <span class="TT3askedBy">
                            A shopper
                            <span class="TT3youHolder" tt3-uid=""></span>

                        </span>


                        <span class="TT3timeStamp">
                            on Feb 4, 2017
                        </span>
                    </div>



                        <div id="TT4bestAnswerBlock-2271251" class="TT4bestAnswerBlock">
                          <div class="TT4ansAndReplies">
                            <div class="TT3ansArea" bestanswer="true">
                              <div class="TT2left TT4ansWidth">
                                <div class="TT3ansCntr">
                                      <div class="TT3itemBox2" style="position:relative">
                                          <div>
                                              <span class="TTbestAnswer">BEST ANSWER:</span> <span id="TT3aText3832066" class="TT3aText">it should work but its still rapidly evolving technology with bios, os and driver support updates rolling out regularly. not to mention firmware for the nvme card its self getting updated. you may get it working with one type of drive and not with another, may need to run in ahci mode, may lose feature support like trim for example is dis-functional in some cases. as for the pci adapter defeating the purpose of m.2 im going to have to disagree. m.2 supports pcie and sata in 1 compact connector, for laptops its the only way to go. its cheaper to make than a full size pcie card drive, and since its what is now in mass mass production its way cheaper. plus if you only have 1 m.2 or need 3 total you need to use an adapter so definitely it has a purpose in that case.</span>
                                              <ul class="TT3linkLine">

                    <div id="TT3answer-3676603" class="TT3ansArea">
                        <div class="TT2left TT4vUpCnt">
                            <a id="TT3vUpLnka3676603" href="javascript:void(0)" rel="nofollow" tt3-uid="8046628" onclick="TurnTo.ilv(1, 3676603, true, this)" title="Up-voting makes sure the good stuff appears first.                         <div class="TT2left TT4respAnsWidth">
                            <div class="TT3ansCntr">
                                <div class="TT3itemBox2" style="position:relative">
                                    <div>
                                        <span id="TT3aText3676603" class="TT3aText">Here is what the GigaByte page says:<br>Dual NVMe PCIe SSDs in RAID 0 Support<br>Ultra-Fast M.2 with PCIe Gen3 x4 &amp; SATA interface<br><br>So, in fact, they are saying that it supports NVMe on PCIe adapters for RAID 0.  It has only one M.2 slot.  In the manual, there is a further limitation noted:<br> "An M.2 PCIe SSD cannot be used to set up a RAID set either with an M.2 SATA SSD or a SATA hard drive"<br><br>Whether you can RAID 0 using the M.2 slot in PCIe mode along with a PCIe M.2 adapter card, I don't know.  IT should be possible and maybe even preferable since some motherboards with have two M.2 slots share the same PCIe lanes between the two slots.....</span>
                                    </div>

                                </div>

        <div id="TT3quest-3398312" class="TT3questWrp TT3questBorder" tt3-uid="10815550" answers="0" date="1519840470000" upvotes="0" downvotes="0" style="display: none;">

                        <span id="TT3qText3398312" class="TT3qText">will it work with the xeon family chip? I am interested in putting a e5-2699 v4 chip.</span>

                    <div class="TT4askedByBlock TT3metaText">

                    <ul class="TT3linkLine TT3questionLinkLine">

    NEG.run(function (require) {
        var jQuery = require("NEG.ThirdParty.JQuery");
        var storage = require("Biz.Storage");
        var viewedItem = storage.getItem("ItemViewed", new Array());
        var shoppingCartItem = Biz.Common.ShoppingItem.extractFromOrderInfo();

        var orderedItem = Web.StateManager.Cookies.get(Web.StateManager.Cookies.Name.PRDLIST, "ItemOrdered");
        var searchKeyword = storage.getItem("ItemSearchKeywords", "");
        var subCookie = function (source, maxlength, delimiter) {
            var result = source;
            if (source) {
                var sourceArray = source.split(delimiter);
                if (sourceArray.length > maxlength) {
                    result = sourceArray.slice(0, maxlength).join(delimiter);
                }
            }
            return result;
        };
        var getParameters = function () {
            var viewedItems = viewedItem.join("#");
            var shoppingCartItems = subCookie(shoppingCartItem, 20, "&");
            var wishlistItems = subCookie(wishlistItem, 20, "&");
            var orderedItems = subCookie(orderedItem, 10, ",");
            var searchKeywords = "";
            if (searchKeyword) {
                var keyValue = searchKeyword.split("|");
                if (keyValue.length >= 2) {
                    searchKeywords = keyValue[1];
                }
            }
            return "v=" + escape(viewedItems) + "&s=" + escape(shoppingCartItems) + "&w=" + escape(wishlistItems) + "&o=" + escape(orderedItems) + "&k=" + escape(searchKeywords);
        };
        var perModules = jQuery("a[href*='Product/ProductList.aspx?Submit=Pers']");
        jQuery.each(perModules, function (index, value) {
            value.href += "&" + getParameters();
        });
    });
</script>

</div>
    </div>
</div>

		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
    if(jQuery('#protect li.primary input').hasClass("zeroDSprice")){
        jQuery('#protect li.primary input.zeroDSprice').attr("checked",true);
        $("driveSaverRadioValueCheck").value = jQuery('#protect li.primary input.zeroDSprice')[0].value;
        if(jQuery('#protect li.secondary').length>0){
            jQuery('#protect li.primary .promo_link').show().addClass('cammo');
            jQuery('#protect li.primary').children('.atnIcon, .note').hide();
        }else{
            jQuery('#protect li.primary .promo_link').hide();
            jQuery('#protect li.primary').children('.atnIcon, .note').show();
        }
    }
    else{
        jQuery('#protect li.primary .promo_link').hide();
    }
    jQuery('#protect li.primary input').click(function(){
        var checkStatus=jQuery(this).attr("checked");
        var _parent=jQuery(this).parent('li');
        if(checkStatus){
            if(_parent.siblings('li.secondary').length > 0){
                _parent.siblings('li.secondary').find('input').attr("checked",!checkStatus);
                _parent.children('.promo_link').show().addClass('cammo');
                _parent.children('.atnIcon, .note').hide();
            }
        } else {
            if(jQuery(this).hasClass("zeroDSprice")){
                jQuery(this).attr("checked",true);
                $("driveSaverRadioValueCheck").value = jQuery('#protect li.primary input.zeroDSprice')[0].value;
            }
            else
            {
                _parent.children('.promo_link').hide().removeClass('cammo');
                _parent.children('.atnIcon, .note').show();
            }
        }
    });
    jQuery('#protect li.primary .promo_link').click(function(){
        var secondary=jQuery(this).parents('ul:not(#protect)').find('li.secondary');
        if(	jQuery(this).parent("li").children('input').attr("checked")) {
            secondary.toggle();
            jQuery(this).parents('ul:not(#protect)').find('li.secondary:last-child').toggleClass("lastchild");
        } else {
            var secondaryCheckStatus=false;
            secondary.each(function() {
                if(jQuery(this).find("input").attr("checked")) {
                    secondaryCheckStatus=true;
                }
            });
            if(!secondaryCheckStatus){
                secondary.toggle();
            }
        }
    });
    jQuery('#protect li.secondary input').click(function() {
        var checkStatus = jQuery(this).attr("checked");
        var _parent = jQuery(this).parent('li');
        if (checkStatus) {
            _parent.siblings('li.primary').find('input').attr("checked", !checkStatus);
            _parent.siblings('li.secondary').find('input').attr("checked", !checkStatus);
        } else {
            _parent.siblings('li.primary').find('input.zeroDSprice').attr("checked", true);
            _parent.siblings('li.secondary').find('input').attr("checked", checkStatus);
        }
    });
</script>

</div>

                <script type="text/javascript">
                    usingNamespace("Biz.Product")["CompareConfig"] = {
                        baseQueryString: new Web.QueryStringBuilder(""),
                        PageUrlAlias: {
                            compare: "https://www.newegg.com/Product/Productcompare.aspx"
                        },
                        compareItems: [],
                        itemThumbs: []
                    };
                    Biz.Product.CompareConfig.compareItems.push("13-128-972");

                <form id="compareform" method="post" action="">
                    <input name="CurrentUrl" id="CurrentUrl" value="" type="hidden">
                </form>
                <script type="text/javascript">
                    NEG.run(function (require) {
                        require("Biz.Product.StepperButton").init();
                    });
                    jQuery(document).ready(function () {
                        var cfg = Biz.Product.CompareConfig;
                        NEG.run(function (require) {
                            var jQuery = require("NEG.ThirdParty.JQuery");
                            var bizCompare = require("Biz.Product.Compare");
                            var options = {
                                goCompare: function () {
                                    document.getElementById('CurrentUrl') && (document.getElementById('CurrentUrl').value = window.location);
                                    var compareData = this.getCompareData();
                                    var compareString = this.getCompareString(compareData);
                                    var items = compareData.itemList;
                                    var itempers = [];

                                    cfg.baseQueryString.set("CompareItemList", compareString);
                                    var citem = "";
                                    var percm = "";
                                    for (var mi = 0; mi < items.length; mi++) {
                                        citem = items[mi];
                                        if (citem != null && citem.length > 0) {
                                            if (itempers[citem] != null && itempers[citem].length > 0) {
                                                percm = percm + ';' + citem + ':' + itempers[citem];
                                            }
                                        }
                                    }
                                    if (percm.length > 0) {
                                        percm = percm.substring(1, percm.length);
                                    }
                                    if (percm.length > 0) {
                                        cfg.baseQueryString.set("percm", encodeURIComponent(percm));
                                    }

                                    var qs = cfg.baseQueryString.toString();
                                    jQuery("#compareform").attr("action",cfg.PageUrlAlias.compare + "?" + qs);
                                    jQuery("#compareform")[0].submit();
                                }
                            };

                            bizCompare(options);
                        });
                    });
                </script>

                <div class="centerPopup-title">
                    <h1>Condition Guidelines <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="fa fa-close button-decline"></a></h1>
                </div>
                <div class="centerPopup-content">
                    <p>The following guidelines apply to all product categories unless otherwise indicated within specific categories.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>New :</strong> This means the product will ship as received by the manufacturer, sealed, with all advertised components, and with the manufacturer warranty.</li>
        <li><strong>Refurbished :</strong> This means the product was tested and repaired as required to meet the standards of the refurbisher, which may or may not be the original manufacturer. Any exceptions to the condition of the item outside the manufacturer’s information should be provided in the listing, up to and including warranty details.</li>
        <li><strong>Open Box :</strong> Newegg only guarantees your receipt of the Open Box product with the purchase of this item. Any accessories <strong>MAY OR MAY NOT</strong> be included. Newegg will NOT send you any missing accessories, even if it is required to use all of the item’s functions.Open Box items usually do not come with manufacturer or vendor warranty or technical support. However, warranty support may be available if an item was never registered by a previous owner. Please contact the manufacturer to check.</li>
        <li><strong>Used - Like New :</strong> This means that the product has been opened, possibly used but is in perfect condition with no signs of cosmetic or functional defect. Product may includes warranty, and accessories found with the original product. Product may or may not be in the original packaging. Returned items with minor packaging defects fall under this category.</li>
        <li><strong>Used - Very Good :</strong> This means that the product has been opened, may show slight signs of use and cosmetic blemish, and may be missing minor accessories, but remain in excellent condition. Product does not come with warranty unless stated otherwise in product description.</li>
        <li><strong>Used - Good :</strong> This means that the product has been used, may show clear signs of use and may be missing minor accessories, but remain in good condition. Product does not come with warranty unless stated otherwise in product description.</li>
        <li><strong>Used - Acceptable :</strong> This means that the product shows clear signs of use, cosmetic defect, and may be missing minor accessories and manual, but remain in working condition. Product does not come with warranty unless stated otherwise in product description. Functionality issues beyond signs of use should be disclosed in product description.</li>
    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
